name: Jimmy Peek
bio: Peek Cycles - One Off Custom Bikes & Parts - Metal Fabrication \m/

social_posts.post_text:
R.I.P. Mr. Pipe Threader. 7 years of rolling sticks. Everything outta Peek Cycles from frames, bars and forks, she finally quit. 

Time for a new one and either they’ve gone up substantially in price over the past 7 years, or I just straight up forgot how pricey they are. 😞 Great timing. Happy Holidays!
Signature Peek Cycles “Twin Peek” Handlebars. 1” OD all the way through per client request. I love the looks of 1” bars all the way through. Thanks for the opportunity Jef! Make it a Killer Day. \m/
#saturdayshopchop #peekcycles #clientorder \m/

One off and quick mock up on the ground to make sure everything checks out. Weld’er up tomorrow and this one goes home to its new owner in Norcal.￼ 

Just a few more frames in the books, you know who you are and I am getting to you! 🙏

This one’s a wrap! Welded up, cleaned up and noodled up, heading home to NorCal! It was a  pleasure meeting and catching up with you @thrillakev ! Enjoy as I look forward to seeing it built up! Maybe SoCal Bike Show?! 😁🤔

A couple handlebar orders headed to Texas completely by chance, Houston and San Antonio. 10” tall Rage2 Bars @ 1”OD and 16” tall Rage1 Bars standard 7/8”OD. Thank fellas for the opportunity. Make it a Killer Day. \m/

1” compound bend Drag bars, well… they were compound bends prior to cutting it up for step downs. 😜 1” OD with standard 7/8” step downs for stem and grips. Thank you @thrillakev for the opportunity. Always appreciated. Make it a Killer Day. \m/

In the tune of Thompson Twins “Lies”… 

Bars, bars, bars… yeah. 🎶 Another busy week, all bars bottom left shipped over the past couple days. Daniel, Andy and Robert, these are yours if you haven’t received them already. 😁

Top left “Double Evil” Tall headed to Leon Emory. And picture right, 1” fatty Clubman, 7/8” grips dropdown with heavy 6” pullback headed to Chad Pruitt. Thank you to everyone for the opportunity. 🙏 Make it a Killer weekend. \m/

Don’t always do Trikes, but when I do…

Bad ass wheels built by @warrenwong5620

New handlebar design, low stance taken from the Peek Cycles Rage bars. 1” fatty’s, 7/8” dropdowns at the stem and grips with deep pullback. Client order, but may have to fab another set for me. 😜 Make it a Killer Day. \m/

Aaaaand… Version B of last weeks “no name” low stance Rage bars. Well, no name yet. Biggest difference from last week, swooped rolled barends versus hard straight bends. I will start making swooped barends available on Rage bars as well. Gonna try it anyway. ￼

1” OD, 7/8” stepdowns at the grips and stem, nice wide stance at 30” to 32”, deep pullback at 8”. These take quite a bit of time and the price will reflect. ￼￼Make it a Killer Day. \m/

First time handlebar design (yes they’re slightly different, short drop barends) and 7/8” OD all the way through. Headed North of the Gate to Juan Chavez for raffle! Be sure to get them tix, bars will include a bit of Peek Schwag, stickers, patch and whatever else I can find. \m/

If fabricating one client one off isn’t enough, then fabricate two simultaneously! Prepping material for tank frame while working the Choppa on the frame jig.

Pretty stoked with the rear dropout design, requested by the client, initial CNC Art by John Lerew at @gearheadcustom, then I designed them to work as rear dropouts with disc brake caliper. 😁

Much more to come! YouTube perhaps? Nonetheless we’re just getting started. Happy Friday! \m/

Client ask, can you fabricate your Lazy Apes at 10” tall using 1.25” diameter tubing with step downs to 7/8”? My reply, I can do whatever you want. ￼And man… I wished I would’ve thought of these, because I want to keep them! 😂 Client later said… oh and throw in a Bent Triple Tree fork! 👊

What is the old saying? Gotta pay to play. Thanks Mike! Hope you like them! \m/
Round trip business today, L.A. and back to drop off this huge triangle for some custom work, then it’ll come back my way to finish the rest of the frame. #iykyk

Another busy Peek Cycles day… and been a while since a personal Peek Cycles build, mainly for reasons of having time. So I recently acquired this of which I’m shooting to have ready for SoCal. No fiberglass, no plastic, all steel. Gonna change things up! Should be fun. Wish me luck! \m/
May the Bent Force… oops… Bent Fork Be With You. #peekcycles #MayTheFork #MayThe4th
Client order “PeekHooks”. Compound bends, 1” OD, dropdowns to 7/8” grips & stem. Make it a Killer Weekend. \m/

First piece of the new build, 20x3 hoop! Thanks to WW! Time to drill out and send to powder! Meanwhile stripping the cart down to body and base for good ol’fashion fabrication and makeover. \m/ #peekcycles

Peek Cycles Cruiser style Knuckle Bars dubbed Cruisin’ for a Bruisin’.

Make it a Killer weekend. \m/ #peekcycles

UPDATE: Not claiming these are the first in the world. 😂 Simply stating that this is the first design to work with Peek Cycles standard and Bent Triple Tree forks, left side mount. 👍

Famous words from the great Han Solo: “She may not look like much, but she's got it where it counts, kid”. New Peek Cycles dropout design, left side mount; 203mm rotor. Yes! Make it a Killer Day. \m/ #peekcycles
Readyfor a jamboree! Busy long day locked & loaded for Riverside tomorrow. \m/

Follow up on the left side mount ￼single piece 203mm brake disc mount/dropouts, designed specifically for Peek Cycles straight or bent triple trees. Pictured on bent fork tubes. Welded up, mocked up and a very pleased with the result. #peekcycles \m/
Working on some bars. \m/ #peekcycles

My entry for the Handlebar Build Off hosted by @tudorbuilt and @datdude20 , “Get a Handle on the Heat” fund raiser. As for the bars, I call them “Knot Easy”. Thanks John @gearheadcustom for dubbing them! 😜 

Been wanting to give these bars a try for some time now, what better opportunity than for a cause. Not my design, but an old school chopper motorcycle pic that’s been floating the interweb for a long time. Credit to the original designer.

Mirrored single piece compound bends, 1” diameter to 7/8” dropdown grips and stem. Knurled stem mount compliments of Joshua at @chopshopcustomz.

Still need to fab up a display base, so I’ll post stills when all said and done. 

Event page on Facebook under “Get a Handle on the Heat”. Also tagged on IG @az_chopaderos_bc Be sure to jump in, give it a follow and grab those raffle tickets! Happy Friday! \m/ #peekcycles

Happy Monster Monday and mail call! Sooo stoked to have this beautiful art piece here at Peek Cycles HQ. Hand sculpted and painted by @lunakustoms out of Kansas. 

Give her social media a look and support local artist far & near. You will not be disappointed. \m/

Thanks again Rochelle! Now to find a bitchin’ spot to hang it!

Client order: Fat 1-1/4” diameter “Rabbit Ears” to standard 7/8” dropdowns at the grips and stem, 1” crossbars top and bottom. Thank you Paul for the opportunity. Make it a Killer Day! \m/ #peekcycles

Fabbed up a single side compound bend stand for the “Knot Easy” build off bars hosted by Gabe Lomeli and Lance Tudor. Simple slide over left grip… boom! 

Thanks to Gabe & Lance for inviting me and all they do for the community. These bars as well as several other bad ass handlebars will be available through raffle at Get a “HANDLE” on the heat with the AZ Chopaderos. So get those raffle tix, do good for the cause and a chance to win some amazing creations. \m/
This lil’ 20x3 drilled out and dropped off at powder this morning to color match the HotRod. Should be fun! \m/ #peekcycles

Client one off. Kind of a takeoff from the Peek “Angel” handlebars with specific geometries and straight back parallel lines to the foreground.￼ Took quite a bit of work to make them happen, happy with the results, so is Chris. 🙏 

Thanks Chris H. for the opportunity. \m/ #peekcycles
What’s Peek been up to? Well… here’s a whole lotta nothin’much. Client order, work in progress, almost there! Make it a Killer Day! ￼\m/ #peekcycles #oneoff #fabricationfriday #dragginass
Been a tad busy and meant to share, finished the chainstays just before the weekend. Coming together, pleased so far, almost there! ￼￼\m/ #peekcycles
Finally gotta late minute to work on my latest project. \m/ #peekcycles
Late night paint progress on the latest Peek frame. 3 more stages. Wish me luck! \m/ #peekcycles
I’m not a painter, but when I do I have fun with it. #peekcycles
Burning the midnight oil, finishing up the new ride! 😁 So looking forward to the weekend! Happy Friday! oh shit! It’s Friday… time to hit the sack! \m/ #peekcycles
We have a roller! #peekcycles \m/
On a little ride SoCal style. #socalbikeshow2023 #peekcycles

Literally finished it Friday morning, first ride SoCal Friday night and all day today, but didn’t take any pics, having too much fun. I managed this pic today, I’ll get more tomorrow at the show. I hope. 😂 Please meet “Sidekick”. 

Thank you @warrenwong5620 for lacing up the 20x3 8g wheel and all three tires. A perfect match!  And thanks to @deltacruiserssa for gifting me the ol’ pedal car. \m/ #peekcycles

HotRod Humpday. Pics and close-ups of my latest project dubbed “Sidekick”. ￼Started out as a vintage 50’s pedal car previously converted to a sidecar for an old Schwinn. 

￼I basically cut everything off using just the body, fabricated a whole new sidecar frame that mounts to the bike via u-bolts so that I have the option of removing it. Diamond plate riveted to cover the holes where the pedal car axles were. Five stage paint starting with wine/rust, black, gray primer, blue then white. Scallops taped off, all patina wet sanded through.

￼36V/250W Hub laced on 20x3 8g spokes built by @warrenwong5620. The “HotRod” bike was fabricated and built 2 years ago, matching 29x3 8g wheels were also built by Warren.

Took it on its maiden ride this past SoCal weekend and rode it all night Friday, all day Saturday. Free beers for everyone! Fun as hell! \m/ #peekcycles #sidecar #sidecars #handbuilt #metalfabrication
I’m no painter, only ever done this a couple times, but when I do I have fun with it. ￼#notrulers  #OlSkool #peekcycles
“Sidekick” Build and how I did it. Complete album on FB. Can only post 10 pics here. #peekcycles #sidecar #sidecars #handbuilt #metalfabrication
SoCal Bike Show last minute Raffle Bars. Congrats once again Alan Solis! Your bars shipped out today! #socalbikeshow2023

Headed your way Home Skillet aka “Jiver”. But there’s no jive when it comes to hand built. #builtnotbought💪 Thank you Joshua… @b.m.f.kustoms @chopshopcustomz from one fabricator to another, I appreciate you. 🙏 \m/

Just a couple of Peek Cycles builds rolling through the beautiful city of Tokyo Japan. 🇯🇵 🙏

It’s a surreal feeling knowing and seeing your work being enjoyed over 5500 miles away. Short video posted by @masayn0720. Full length video on Masa’s IG account.

Thank you Masamitsu, Jérôme and the rest of the crew for the support. Much respect. Always appreciated. 🙏 \m/
Well… I never thought I’d run one of these down, but I did. The original grill for my 50’s Sidecar. Going to paint it to match with a little buttoning up soon to come! ￼😁 \m/ #peekcycles
Late night post workin’ on the Sidekick. New to me, original vintage grill on the sidecar and we now have lights! Pretty stoked on the new look and purpose. They see me rollin! 👀😁 #peekcycles \m/
Happy Cranksgiving from the Peek’s!

Peek Cycles recently tagged on another shot out of Tokyo Japan. 🇯🇵 Peek T2 Frame, Double Evil Bars and Signature PC Triple Tree Forks. \m/ Thank you @slowcycle_theothersbc for the love and support! 🙏 #blessed #grateful #onelove #peekcycles

Once upon a time in 2018, and hard to believe we recently past the 5 year mark. Peek Cycles one off designed and still owned by Leon Taylor. This bike looks fast sittin’ still. Beautiful build and concept, never get tired looking at it. Thanks again for the opportunity. 🙏 #peekcycles
